  "description": [
    "C2 MASONS 10 OPEN BIENNIAL SESSION Meetings of Scottish Rite Council Start Sunday To Last Week The Supreme Council Ancient and Accepted Scottish Rite of the Southern Jurisdiction will convene in biennial session at the House of the Temple the home of the Southern Supreme Council beginning Sunday Sessions will con tinue all week At the forthcoming sessions many features of general interest to membeis of the Scottish Rite as well as of the other orders of Freemasonry will be considered These embrace the Albert Pike memorial service on the opening day when the address on the life and works of the great Scottish Rite student and philosopher Gen Pike will be de livered by Louis Block of Davenport lowa one of the youngest members of the Supreme Council In point of serv ice Grand Comdr John H Cowlea will preside the session beginning at 3 oclock in the afternoon To Confer 33rd Degree Two important events of the session will be the investiture of the rank and decoration of knight commander of the court of honor and the conferring of the thirtythird degree upon outstand ing Masons A trip to Mount Vernon is scheduled next Sunday and an organ"
